post_text:
Section 7 Fall sports update:
Just a Quick update to keep you in the loop.
Last night NYSPHAA announced that they have delayed the start of Volleyball and Cheerleading until March 2021. Section 7 has had several meetings since we last posted. There are 3 meetings planned over the next 3 days with the Section 7 Executive Director, Section 7 Athletic Council, Superintendents and Athletic Directors. After Tuesday there may be some more concrete decisions on where section 7 is heading with fall sports. Stay tuned.

Dear MS/HS Parents,
If you decided to have your student participate in full time remote learning for the start of the school year. The courses your child will be responsible for can be found on the their SchoolTool schedule, and the work provided will be given by the teachers on their schedules. Because this material will be accessed remotely, it will be important to be in contact with each individual teacher as they will need to communicate with you how their course will be delivered to your student. Students should be checking their school emails for more specific details in the coming days. Remote learning will begin on September 8, 2020. If you have any questions please contact NACS Middle High School at 518-594-3962.

post_text:
Today Governor Cuomo provided an update regarding interscholastic athletics. This announcement has created both both general and sport specific questions that we do no have definite answers to at this time. Here is the timeline that the New York State Public High School Athletic Association (NYSPHSAA) will be following:

Within 24 hours – Executive Director Meeting
Within 48 hours – NYSPHSAA Task Force Meeting
Within 72 hours – NYSPHSAA Officers will make official decisions if need be.

Hopefully within the next week NYSPHSAA and the DOH will clarify what this means for our fall sports season.

Congratulations to all our graduates and their families. Enjoy the rest of the summer and we will see you in high school next year.

post_text:
****8th grade graduation and Graduation train update****

In trying to make the most efficient routes for our graduation train, we realize that it does not allow parents adequate time to adjust their work schedules for our arrival. We had hoped to have the graduation train on Wednesday and Thursday of this week but we have pushed that until Monday and Tuesday of next week, to accommodate our families. We plan to start the train each day at 9am. We will post the graduation train route on Facebook and our website tomorrow. In light of this change we will move our virtual graduation ceremony and post it for your viewing pleasure on this Thursday evening. Thank you for your patience with this process.

Hey Bobcats, here is a special statement from the Governor:

Special Statement – Monday, June 8, 2020
Governor Andrew Cuomo issued Executive Order No.202.39 today and it has changed the Annual School District Elections in the following ways.
The ballots will remain unopened until Tuesday, June 16, 2020 at 5pm
No ballots will be accepted by the District Clerk in person after Tuesday, June 9, 2020 at 5pm
The District Drop-box for ballots will be closed at 5pm on Tuesday, June 9, 2020
Ballots that are mailed in and received by 5pm on Tuesday, June 16, 2020 will be included in the canvassing process

To read the Executive Order in its entirety you may go to the following link; https://www.governor.ny.gov/news/no-20239-continuing-temporary-suspension-and-modification-laws-relating-disaster-emergency

post_text:
Attention: All Qualified NACSD Voters Important Notice on Absentee Ballot Voting

In order for your Absentee Ballot to be considered "eligible to process", both sides of the envelope must be completed, to include the signature and date on the back side of the envelope. This will allow the poll workers to verify the voter's eligibility against the Voter Registration Log provided by the Clinton County Board of Elections.
If you have already sent your ballot in, without completion and signature, please contact the District Clerk at 594-7060 X2501 to request additional ballot(s) be sent to you. Unsigned envelopes will NOT be able to be processed.

post_text:
Attention all PO Box holders in the Northern Adirondack School District:

If you currently receive your mail at a PO Box, you most likely will not receive a School Budget Ballot. This is due to the fact that the Board of Elections only uses physical addresses for their elections. This is the list we used for our School Budget Vote. If you did not receive a school ballot, please call the school at 518-594-7060 x2501 to request one and we will mail you a ballot. Also, if you have any questions, do not hesitate to contact me. Thank you, Helen Yelle District Clerk.

post_text: Good afternoon Northern Adirondack Families! On Friday, March 27th Governor Andrew Cuomo announced that all public schools in New York State will remain closed until April 15th. This new Executive Order supersedes all previous notifications, including those issued by the Northern Adirondack Central School District. We will follow this order, and all subsequent orders, as set forth and continue to provide remote instruction, meals to students, as well as child care for essential workers every weekday through April 14th. Thank you for continuing to support us.

Hey Bobcats, We realize that while we are out of school to do our part in reducing the spread of the COVID-19, many of our students do not have access to their counselors. In an effort to help serve our students while we are out of school we are providing our students with the opportunity to speak to or leave a message for our counselors.

Between the hours of 8:00am - 3:00pm Monday through Friday the NAC counselors can be reached by phone at:

Mrs. Hayes, (518)-912-4437
Mrs. Brudvig (518)-257-6543
Mr. McAfee (518)-903-9208
Mrs. Gregory (518)-912-4486
Mrs. Hoff (518)-912-4493

If you are in crisis and have an emergency, please call 911 or the 24 hour crisis line 1-866-5PREVENT. The Crisis Text Line is the free, 24/7, confidential text message service for people in crisis. Text HOME to 741741

Please know that we are trying our best to continue to serve our students during this uncertain time, take care.

It is important that we all stay happy and healthy this week. We want to help keep the kids engaged and keep them challenged. We will be posting some cool stuff we find online this week that will try to help our NAC Family to navigate through this crazy time. Please message us if there is anything we can do to help. Even though we can't all BE together, we are IN THIS TOGETHER. 💚

post_text: Hello Bobcats! We are receiving hearsay/rumors that the school district is closing or taking some other action regarding COVID -19, it is not true. If there is any action by the district you will be hearing from Mr. Knight the superintendent. Until you hear from Mr. Knight, please disregard any rumors or hearsay. We are working with the Health Department, the CVES District Superintendent, Dr. Davey, and the State Education Department regarding the best ways to serve our community. We continue to exercise precautionary measures to keep our students safe and continue their education. We understand the heightened sense of anxiety due to the pandemic and ongoing decisions being made by the federal and state government and will keep our community safe and informed as quickly as possible. Thank you for your patience.

post_text: The Northern Adirondack Central School District has two School Board seats open for the 2020-21 school year. The term is for five years; the seats are currently held by Phalon Miner and Shirley Durnin. Candidates who’d like to seek a position must be: a qualified voter of the district; a U.S. citizen; at least 18 years old; and a resident of the district for at least one year before the election. Also, board members may not reside with a family member who is presently on the School Board, and they can’t be an employee of the school. Those who would like to be considered as candidates for this term must submit a petition to District Clerk Helen Yelle signed by at least 25 qualified voters of the district. Petitions may be submitted 8 AM to 3:30 PM Monday through Friday at the District Office, 5572 Route 11Ellenburg Depot. The deadline is 5 PM Monday, April 20, 2020 when the office will stay open to accept final submissions. Find petitions forms at www.nacs1.org or at the District Office. Call 594-7060 x2501 to have a petition mailed to you.

Hey Bobcats! Big game tonight at 7:45 in Beekmantown, the girls' varsity basketball team is playing Ticonderoga for the sectional championship!

Congratulations to our Varsity Cheer Team for their Sectional win Friday night! On to the State Championships!

Congratulations to the boys varsity basketball for an outstanding win over Saranac Lake Saturday! They are on to the Sectional game against Ausable Valley Tuesday March 3, 2020 at 6:00pm in Beekmantown!

The Saranac Varsity Hockey Team (Nolan Knight) will be playing the Saranac Lake/Lake Placid team Wednesday March 4, 2020 at the Ronald B. Stafford Ice Arena at 7:45, Wednesday Night!

Congrats to all the FFA teams competing at Districts this weekend, All of the teams are moving on to Sub-States!

A final congratulations to Tyler Trombley (182) for a great showing at the State Wrestling Championships!
